fontStrategy:
SF Pro is licensed for use on Apple platforms only, so we do NOT ship SF Pro woff files. Instead we expose a wordmark-grade SF stack and let the OS provide the real faces locally, with a robust cross-platform fallback so non-Apple users still get a near-identical sans.

(1) @font-face local() bridge — gives us named families `OB Display` / `OB Text` that resolve to the locally installed SF Pro on this macOS build machine and on visitors' Apple devices, with graceful degradation:

@font-face{font-family:'OB Display';src:local('SF Pro Display'),local('SFProDisplay-Regular'),local('-apple-system');font-weight:400 700;font-display:swap;}
@font-face{font-family:'OB Text';src:local('SF Pro Text'),local('SFProText-Regular'),local('-apple-system');font-weight:400 600;font-display:swap;}

(2) CSS custom properties drive everything:
  --font-display:'OB Display','SF Pro Display',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',system-ui,sans-serif;
  --font-text:'OB Text','SF Pro Text',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',system-ui,sans-serif;
  --font-mono:'SF Mono','SFMono-Regular',ui-monospace,'Menlo','Cascadia Code','Roboto Mono',monospace;
Headings use var(--font-display); body uses var(--font-text); code/numerals use var(--font-mono).

(3) Tailwind wiring — extend theme.fontFamily: display:['var(--font-display)'], sans:['var(--font-text)'], mono:['var(--font-mono)']. We deliberately do NOT use next/font/google (no Inter/Roboto — that violates brand DNA). The existing Geist woff files in src/app/fonts are removed/ignored.

(4) Optical sizing & rendering: set `font-optical-sizing:auto`, `-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased`, `text-rendering:optimizeLegibility`. SF Pro Display auto-engages on >=20px sizes (Apple's optical cut) which is why the scale assigns Display to title-1 and up.

(5) Numerals: SF Mono via `font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums` on counters/timers/scores; SF Pro Text otherwise. SF Pro's default lining figures are fine for body.

(6) Dyslexia-friendly toggle: a fourth family `--font-dyslexic`. We self-host OpenDyslexic (open SIL license, safe to ship) as woff2 in /public/fonts and, when [data-dyslexia='on'] is set on <html>, swap --font-text and --font-display to var(--font-dyslexic) while keeping the type scale, color, and layout intact. Mono stays mono for code integrity. Fallback chain: 'OpenDyslexic','Comic Sans MS',var(--font-text). The toggle also bumps letter-spacing and line-height (see Accessibility).

(7) Performance: families are system-local first so first paint needs zero network for Apple users; only OpenDyslexic (opt-in) and SF Mono fallbacks ever download. font-display:swap prevents invisible-text flashes.
